frameDefinitions: A Recipient starts off without the Theme in their possession, and then comes to possess it.
An Entity ends up in a Final_category, Final_situation, or Final_quality which it was not in before.
An Experiencer, Expressor, or State can be described as characterized as having an emotion of fear concerning a particular Topic or as evoked by a Stimulus.
An Event takes place at a Place and Time.
After a period in which the Agent has been working on a Goal, the Agent manages to attain it.
This frame has to do with nouns denoting types of entities.
frameExamples: I was <t>scared</t> by a bump in the night.
Big earthquakes only <t>happen</t> along plate boundaries. INI
I don't like this newfangled <t><fex name='Subtype'>kind</fex></t> of  fish.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Recipient</fen> indicates the entity that ends up in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes possession.
When the event occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> denotes where the Getting takes place.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which undergoes a change, ending up in the <fen>Final_category</fen>, <fen>Final_situation</fen>, or <fen>Final_quality</fen>.
The quality of the <fen>Entity</fen> after the change.
The category that the <fen>Entity</fen> ends up in after the change.
The <fen>Entity</fen>'s situation after the change.
When the change occurs.
Where the change takes place.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> is the person or sentient entity that experiences or feels the emotions.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the general area in which the emotion occurs.  It indicates a range of possible <fen>Stimulus</fen>.
The <fen>Stimulus</fen> is the person, event, or state of affairs that evokes the emotional response in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.

The body part, gesture, or other expression of the <fen>Experiencer</fen> that reflects his or her emotional state.  They describe a presentation of the experience or emotion denoted by the adjective or noun.
The <fen>State</fen> is the abstract noun that describes a more lasting experience by the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Experiencer</fen>, <fen>Expressor</fen>, or <fen>State</fen> can be described as having said emotion.
Name of the event which occurs.
Where the event takes place.
When the event occurs.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs the intentional act that fulfills the <fen>Goal</fen>.
The state or action that the <fen>Agent</fen> has wished to participate in.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> achieves their <fen>Goal</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> achieves their <fen>Goal</fen>.
The entity which denotes a subtype of the more general <fen>Category</fen>.
The more general type that the target denotes a subtype of. This role is obligatory and should be labeled DNI when not present.
listRoleExamples: He never could understand how she ended up <fex>an evangelist</fex>.
My father got <fex>to where he did in the business</fex> through instinct and entrepreneurialism.
<fex>By 1945</fex> he had become uncertain of the advisability of anyone having such a weapon.
Iraq had achieved <fex>its programme objective of producing nuclear weapons</fex> .
<fex>By 1700</fex> , our forces will have achieved total victory .
She had already achieved that feat <fex>in Burma</fex> .
I don't like this <fex>kind</fex> of fish.
They created a new breed <fex>of dog</fex>.
